instructions1:
Instructions:
Please read the following instructions carefully. On the next page, you will be asked a question about the information in these instructions. Incorrect responses will result in the survey exiting, and you will not receive a payment code for Mechanical Turk.

 
Task:

You will look at graphs like the one below and then answer questions about them. These graphs will show trends over time in different cities. Each graph shows a trend for a different city.​

 



 
 

 
 

Based on these trends, you will be asked: "What can you say about the situation in this city?" You will click inside one of the boxes to select your preferred judgment.
trick:
Complete the sentence with the appropriate 7 letter word:  


During this study, it is important that you make your judgments as  _ _ _ _ _ _ _ and accurately as possible.  

 

Please enter your response in the text box using only lower case letters.

GL1:
Here is some information about cancer therapies.
​

What percentage of patients recovered after chemotherapy?
GL2: What is the difference between the percentage of patients who recovered after a surgery and the percentage of patients who recovered after radiation therapy?
GL3:
​Here is some information about different forms of cancer.




Of all the people who die from cancer, approximately what percentage dies from lung cancer?
GL4: Approximately what percentage of people who die from cancer die from colon cancer, breast cancer, and prostate cancer taken together?
GL5:
Here is some information about an imaginary disease called Adeolitis.



Approximately what percentage of people had Adeolitis in the year 2000?
GL6: When was the increase in the percentage of people with Adeolitis higher?
GL7: According to your best guess, what will the percentage of people with Adeolitis be in the year 2010?
GL8:
​The following figure shows the number of men and women among the patients with disease X. The total number of circles is 100. 


​

Of the 100 patients with disease X, how many are women?
GL9: How many more men than women are there among the 100 patients with disease X?
GL10:
In a magazine, you see two advertisements, one on page 5 and another on page 12. Each is for a different drug for treating heart disease, and each includes a graph showing the effectiveness of the drug compared to a placebo (sugar pill).
​



Compared to the placebo, which treatment leads to a larger decrease in the percentage of patients who die?
GL11:
In the newspaper, you see two advertisements, one on page 15 and another on page 17. Each is for a different treatment of psoriasis, and each includes a graph showing the effectiveness of the treatment over time.
​


Which of the treatments contributes to a larger decrease in the percentage of sick patients?
GL12:
Here is some information about the imaginary diseases Coliosis and Tiosis.




Between 1980 and 1990, which disease had a higher increase in the percentage of people affected?
GL13:
Here is some information about cancer therapies.  

What is the percentage of the cancer patients who die after chemotherapy?
